I was part of the team that worked on the original pc version, and technology has finally caught up with these groundbreaking games! So nice to play them again. Great problem solving skills and analytical thinking can be learned by playing them. Don't try to skip over anything: listen, read, collect and talk to everyone. Try out everything, that is the whole point to the gameplay. It's all about a child exploring the world these games present...click on the rocks, the scenery, decorations, shells, pull cords, move things, leave NOTHING untried.
